  "articleSummary": "The article argues that large language models are fundamentally probabilistic pattern-matching engines, not computational tools, making them inherently unreliable for mathematical tasks despite their linguistic fluency. Rather than waiting for architectural improvements, developers should offload arithmetic and symbolic computation to dedicated engines using modern tool-calling frameworks. The author provides a practical TypeScript implementation leveraging the AI SDK v5/v6 and CortexJS Compute Engine, emphasizing batch processing, explicit tool descriptions, and robust error handling for reliable integration. Written in a direct, problem-solution tone and framed around the metaphor of a \"gymnast balancing a checkbook,\" the piece targets AI application developers and software engineers building LLM-powered systems that require precise mathematical capabilities.",
